718114f-a.title: Manhattan: Carmine Street - Bedford Street
718114f-a.text:
51-59 Carmine Street, at and adjoining the N.W. corner of
Bedford Street.
March 6, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same four buildings after drastic alterations. This
view also shows the west side of Bedford Street all the way to
Leroy Street and Seventh Avenue South.
March 27, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.

718115f-a.title: Manhattan: Carmine Street - Bedford Street
718115f-a.text:
Carmine Street, north from Bedford Street. Before Seventh
Avenue South was cut in 1915, Carmine Street was the connecting
link between the northern end of Varick Street and the southern
end of Sixth Avenue. At one time the Varick Street surface line
continued over Carmine Street to and up Sixth Avenue.
April 3, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
Carmine St., n.e., from Bedford St. Neg. A-111
P.L. Sperr, photographer  May 14, 1941
